{{Infobox Journal | title = Journal of Medieval Religious Cultures | cover = JMRC_cov.jpg | editor = Christine F. Cooper-Rompato, Robert Hasenfratz | discipline = [[Mysticism]], [[history]] | formernames = Mystics Quarterly, 14th Century English Mystics Newsletter | abbreviation = J. Mediev. Religious Cult. | publisher = [[Penn State University Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Biannually | history = 1974-present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.psupress.org/journals/jnls_jmrc.html | link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/journal_of_medieval_religious_cultures/ | link1-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = 19476566 | OCLC = 316799057 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1947-6566 | eISSN = 2153-9650 }} The '''''Journal of Medieval Religious Cultures''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes essays on mystical and devotional texts, especially from the Western [[Middle Ages]]. It is published twice a year by [[Penn State University Press]]. The journal previously went by the names ''14th Century English Mystics Newsletter'' (1974-1983) and ''Mystics Quarterly'' (1984-2008).
